<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Gravity_Entertainment">Gravity Entertainment</span></h2>


<ul>
<li>  - </li></ul>
<p>An article on a movie production firm. Various IP&#39;s and new accounts are repeatedly inserting allegations of criminal conduct by company employees, referenced only by blog entries, which fail <a href="" title="WP:RS">WP:RS</a>. Although the article itself is not a biography, the BLP guidelines indicate the policy applies to biographical material about living persons on any page. </p>
<p>There&#39;s been a cycle of adding and removing the material - I locked the page for a week to encourage discussion, but the blog-referenced allegations were simply restored as soon as protection expired. I&#39;m considering a longer-term semi-protection but wanted to bring it here for additional sets of eyes first.   <a href="" title="User:Euryalus">Euryalus</a> (<a href="" title="User talk:Euryalus">talk</a>) 03:47, 3 April 2009 (UTC)</p>

